com.github.glusk2.sprouts.core.snapshots

Class TouchEventSnapshooter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.badlogic.gdx.scenes.scene2d.InputListener
      • com.github.glusk2.sprouts.core.snapshots.TouchEventSnapshooter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, Snapshooter

    public final class TouchEventSnapshooter
extends InputListener
implements Snapshooter
    A TouchEventSnapshooter is a special kind of "camera" that takes "pictures" of the game board state on every touch event.

    This is a mutable object that re-directs InputListener's touch events to the encapsulated initialSnapshot object.

    snapshot() returns the updated initialSnapshot after zero or more touch events.
